snippet: LEAD: A summer campaign of logging protests has left the communities along California's northern coast more polarized over the issue of saving trees versus saving jobs and may even have caused a schism in the group leading the protests....
lead_paragraph: LEAD: A summer campaign of logging protests has left the communities along California's northern coast more polarized over the issue of saving trees versus saving jobs and may even have caused a schism in the group leading the protests.

headline.main: One Result of Logging Protests: More Antagonism

byline.original: By KATHERINE BISHOP, Special to The New York Times
